{"lemma":"سُوء","slug":"سُوء","root":"س.#.#","root_slug":"س-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سُوء","root":"سوأ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":50},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21124","n21125"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَاءَ (sāʔa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evil, badness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evil, badness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"calamity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"malice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"treachery"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hell"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare سَيِّئ (sayyiʔ, “evil, bad”)."},"ipa":["/sawʔ/","/suːʔ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21124","headword_ar":"سَوْءٌ","root":"swA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA='a","text_ar":"سَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S, M, K,) intrans., (Lth, M,) and trans.: (S, M, K:) and is also used as an epithet, applied to a man, (M, Msb, and Ham p. 712,) and to an action. (Msb.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulu sawo'K","text_ar":"رَجُلُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man of evil nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man who does what is evil, displeasing, grievous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vexatious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulu Als~awo'i","text_ar":"رَجُلُ السَّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the man of evil nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doings"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (S, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iy^obu Als~awo'i","text_ar":"ذِيْبُ السَّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wolf of evil nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], as in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAla","text_ar":"اَحَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwl","text_ar":"حول"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamalu sawo'K","text_ar":"عَمَلُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deed of evil nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamalu Als~awo'i","text_ar":"عَمَلُ السَّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the deed of evil nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ham p. 498:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEotu sawo'K","text_ar":"نَعْتُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an epithet of evil nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sHq","text_ar":"سحق"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEofu sawo'K","text_ar":"سَعْفُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bad commodity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEf","text_ar":"سعف"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and if you make the former word determinate [by means of the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"], you use the latter as an epithet [also], (M, * Msb, and Ham, p. 712, *) and you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajulu Als~awo'u","text_ar":"الرَّجُلُ السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the evil man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the man who does what is evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Msb, and Ham p. 712:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEamalu Als~awo'u","text_ar":"العَمَلُ السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the evil deed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) [this last phrase I hold to be correct, regarding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awo'u","text_ar":"السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this case as originally an inf. n. of the intrans. verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA='a","text_ar":"سَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore capable of being used as an epithet applied to anything; though] IB says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awo'u","text_ar":"السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as an epithet is applied to a man but not to a deed: (TA:) [in what here follows from the S, denying the correctness of another phrase mentioned above on the authority of lexicologists of high repute, there is, in my opinion, an obvious mistranscription, twice occurring,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awo'u","text_ar":"السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwo'u","text_ar":"السُّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I suppose to have passed from an early copy of that work into most other copies thereof, for I find it alike in all to which I have had access:] Akh says, one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajulu Als~awo'u","text_ar":"الرَّجُلُ السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~u Alyaqiynu","text_ar":"الحَقُّ اليَقِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~u Alyaqiyni","text_ar":"حَقُّ اليَقِينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awo'u","text_ar":"السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyaqiynu","text_ar":"اليَقِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~u","text_ar":"الحَقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": he says, also, nor should one say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulu Als~uwo'i","text_ar":"رَجُلُ السُّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with damm: (S:) [here the expres-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1458},{"kind":"text","text":"sion “ with damm ” may perhaps be meant to refer to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alsw'","text_ar":"السوء"},{"kind":"text","text":"in all of the three instances above; not in the last only:] IB says, [in remarking on this passage of the S, in which he appears to have read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwo'","text_ar":"السُّوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, in all of the three instances,] Akh allows one's saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulu Als~awo'i","text_ar":"رَجُلُ السَّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulu sawo'K","text_ar":"رَجُلُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"in both; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulu Als~uwo'i","text_ar":"رَجُلُ السُّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":", because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwo'u","text_ar":"السُّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst., meaning “ harm, injury, hurt, mischief, or damage, ” and “ evilness of state or condition; ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajul","text_ar":"رَجُل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is prefixed, as governing a gen. case, only to the inf. n.: and he adds that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Alr~ajulu Als~awo'u","text_ar":"هٰذَا الرَّجُلُ السَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not prefixing [the former noun to the latter, but using the latter as an epithet]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also the next paragraph, in six places."}],"source_refs":["Lth","S","M","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21125","headword_ar":"سُوْءٌ","root":"swA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA='ahu","text_ar":"سَا=ءَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, * K;) [so, app., accord. to the generality of the lexicologists;] or inf. n. (Ksh and Bd in ii. 46) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~iy^N","text_ar":"سَيِّيٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ksh ibid.,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA='a","text_ar":"سَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasuwo'u","text_ar":"يَسُوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd ibid.,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA='ahu","text_ar":"سَا=ءَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (TA;) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evilness, badness, abominableness, foulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unseemliness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"displeasingness, grievousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vexatiousness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as, for instance, of natural disposition, and of doings: (Ksh ubi suprà:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitious, immoral, unrighteous, sinful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked, conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAhu bisuwo'K","text_ar":"رَمَاهُ بِسُوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rmy","text_ar":"رمي"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything disapproved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disallowed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regarded as evil, bad, abominable, foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unseemly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evil action"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evilness of state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition: harm, injury, hurt, mischief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"damage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is mentioned as being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~iy^","text_ar":"سَيِّي"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Lth, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any evil, evil affection, cause of mischief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harm"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injury, noxious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destructive thing, calamity, disease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malady:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowaA='N","text_ar":"اَسْوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to a general rule.] The saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^unokiruka mino suwo'K","text_ar":"مَا اُنْكِرُكَ مِنْ سُوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I do not disacknowledge thee in consequence of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwo'","text_ar":"سُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evilness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] that I have seen in thee, but only in consequence of my little knowledge of thee. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"linaSorifa Eanohu Als~uwo'a","text_ar":"لِنَصْرِفَ عَنْهُ السُّوْءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlfaHo$aA='a","text_ar":"وَالفَحْشَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xii. 24], is said by Zj to mean, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In order that we might turn away from him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unfaithfulness to his master, and adultery."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwo'u AlHisaAbi","text_ar":"سُوْءُ الحِسَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xiii. 18, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The evilness of the reckoning"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is expl. by him as meaning a reckoning in which no good work will be accepted, and no evil work passed over; because infidelity will have made the former to be of no avail: or, as some say, it means a reckoning pursued to the utmost extent, in which no evil work will be passed over. (M, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA","text_ar":"لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayora fiY qawoli Als~uwo'i","text_ar":"خَيْرَ فِى قَوْلِ السُّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no good in"},{"kind":"text","text":"thy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwo'","text_ar":"سُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is evil;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwl","text_ar":"قول"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here used in its original sense of an inf. n.]: but if you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awo'","text_ar":"السَّوْء","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [you use"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwl","text_ar":"قول"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maquwl","text_ar":"مَقُول"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in evil speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA as from the K, but not in the CK nor in my MS. copy of the K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwo'N","text_ar":"سُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to one reading, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawo'N","text_ar":"سَوْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to another, (K, TA, [but all that is given in this sentence as from the K is so given only on the authority of the TA, not being in the CK nor in my MS. copy of the K]) the latter of which readings is the more common, (TA,) in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irapu Als~w'","text_ar":"دَايِرَةُ السّوء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) in the Kur [ix. 99 and xlviii. 6], (TA,) mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Defeat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affliction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"torment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perdition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destruction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corruption:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and in like manner in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umoTirato maTara Als~w'i","text_ar":"اُمْطِرَتْ مَطَرَ السّوءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) in the Kur [xxv. 42]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwo'","text_ar":"السُّوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harm, injury, hurt, mischief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"damage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evilness of state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as expl. before;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awo'","text_ar":"السَّوْء","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corruption,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destruction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perdition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwo'","text_ar":"السُّوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irapu Als~uwo'i","text_ar":"دَايِرَةُ السُّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defeat"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the reading ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awo'","text_ar":"السَّوْء","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is from [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasaA='ap","text_ar":"المَسَا=ءَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as inf. n.]. (S. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irapN","text_ar":"دَايِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwr","text_ar":"دور"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Accord. to Zj, in the saying in the Kur [xlviii. 6], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@lZ~aAn~iyna biA@ll~`hi Zan~a A@ls~awo'i","text_ar":"ا@لظَّانِّينَ بِا@للّٰهِ ظَنَّ ا@لسَّوْءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~a AlA^amori Als~awo'i","text_ar":"ظَنَّ الاَمْرِ السَّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who opine, of God, the opining of the evil thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Bd,) it is allowable to read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~a Als~uwo'i","text_ar":"ظَنَّ السُّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, TA;) and thus some read in this instance: (Jel:) but AM says, in the saying in the Kur [xlviii. 12], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waZananotumo Zan~a Als~awo'i","text_ar":"وَظَنَنْتُمْ ظَنَّ السَّوْءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And ye opined the evil opining"},{"kind":"text","text":"], it is read only with fet-h, and damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not allowable in this instance, for there is in it no meaning of trial, or affliction, and torment: (TA:) [for this distinction, however, I see no reason; and it is not correct; for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alsw'","text_ar":"السوء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with fet-h and with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the three sentences [whereof this last is one] in which it occurs in this chapter. (Jel.) ―         -b2-  In the Kur vii. 188, it is said to mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diabolical possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insanity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"madness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leprosy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraSN","text_ar":"بَرَصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S, M, K, TA,) is said to be its meaning in the Kur xx. 23 and xxvii. 12 and xxviii. 32. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur xxx. 9, accord. to the reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwo'a","text_ar":"السُّوْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) said to mean there"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the reading commonly known is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwo'aY","text_ar":"السُّوْءَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness in the eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [Thus, i. e. with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the CK and TK: in the TA said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAlftH","text_ar":"بالفتح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is evidently a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAlDm~","text_ar":"بالضمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","IB","Lth","M","K","Bd","Jel"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}